class KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
Static helpers for attaching Kadas-specific per-item metadata (editor
widget name, tooltip) to a stock \c :py:class:`QgsAnnotationLayer`.

Stock \c :py:class:`QgsAnnotationItem` subclasses do not expose a
custom-property bag, so per-instance metadata that Kadas needs (and
which has no upstream equivalent) is stored on the owning layer instead.
This keeps the items themselves stock and round-trippable through
vanilla QGIS, at the cost of losing metadata when an item is moved
between layers (which Kadas does not currently allow from the UI).

Storage schema: each datum is stored as a layer custom property keyed
<tt>kadas:item-meta:&lt;itemId&gt;:&lt;field&gt;</tt>. Project save/load
preserves these because layer custom properties are part of the standard
QGIS layer XML.
%End

%TypeHeaderCode
#include "kadas/gui/annotationitems/kadasannotationlayerhelpers.h"
%End
  public:
    static QString tooltip( const QgsAnnotationLayer *layer, const QString &itemId );
%Docstring
string if none is set.
%End

    static void setTooltip( QgsAnnotationLayer *layer, const QString &itemId, const QString &tooltip );
%Docstring
``tooltip`` removes it.
%End

    static QgsAnnotationLayer *createLayer( const QString &name, const QgsCoordinateReferenceSystem &preferredCrs = QgsCoordinateReferenceSystem() );
%Docstring
Creates a new \c :py:class:`QgsAnnotationLayer` named ``name``. If
``preferredCrs`` is valid it is used as the layer CRS (so callers
importing data in a known native CRS can avoid round-trip reprojection).
Otherwise the current project CRS is used, falling back to EPSG:3857 if
the project has no CRS. The returned layer is NOT added to the project;
the caller is expected to call \c
:py:func:`QgsProject.instance()`->:py:func:`~KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.addMapLayer`.
%End

    static void prepareLayerForSave( QgsAnnotationLayer *layer );
%Docstring
For every Kadas master annotation item in ``layer`` that has a
registered controller exposing \c
:py:func:`~KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.generateShadows`, creates the
shadow items, inserts them into the layer, and stores their ids on the
master via \c :py:func:`~KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.setShadowIds`.
Idempotent: existing shadows referenced by the master are stripped first
to avoid accumulation across repeated saves.

Intended to be called immediately before \c
:py:func:`QgsProject.write()`.
%End

    static void stripShadowsFromLayer( QgsAnnotationLayer *layer );
%Docstring
For every Kadas master annotation item in ``layer`` that has non-empty
\c :py:func:`~KadasAnnotationLayerHelpers.shadowIds`, removes the
referenced shadow items from the layer and clears the master's shadow id
list.

Intended to be called immediately after \c :py:func:`QgsProject.write()`
(to leave the in-memory layer pristine for the running session) and
after \c :py:func:`QgsProject.read()` (to drop any shadows that survived
the round-trip when the project was saved by a previous Kadas session).
%End

};

